						<summary>

						<p>On a stone built into the wall of the kitchen in the Viśvanāthasvāmīn temple.</p>						

						<p>Adhirājēndra. Year 3: 1070-71 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This fragmentary inscription contains a portion of the <hi rend="italic">praśasti, Tiṅgaḷēr malarndu</hi> of the king.</p>						

						<p>This records a gift of land for cultivating a garden. Mīmalai Jayaṅgoṇḍaśōḻa chaturvēdimaṅgalam in Vīrarājēndra-vaḷanāḍu is also mentioned.</p>						

						</summary>
